    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="8">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302954">Figure 54</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302954" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302954" filename="../figg13/g1302954.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Input Shaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts retaining the front bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302955">inset, Figure 55</hotlnk>). Remove the bearing cap, gasket and O-ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302955" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302955" filename="../figg13/g1302955.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Remove Bolts Retaining Front Bearing Cover and Remove Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing retaining snap ring from the groove in the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302956">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302956" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302956" filename="../figg13/g1302956.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Remove Bearing Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push down on the input shaft to cock the bearing in the bore. Drive the input shaft toward
                the rear of the transmission, through the bearing as far as possible (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302957">Figure 57</hotlnk>). Pull the input shaft forward to expose the snap ring of
                the bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302957" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302957" filename="../figg13/g1302957.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Drive Input Shaft Toward Rear of Transmission</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to complete removal of the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302958">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302958" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302958" filename="../figg13/g1302958.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Complete Bearing Removal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear spacer and snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302959">inset, Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302959" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302959" filename="../figg13/g1302959.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Remove Drive Gear Spacer and Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward and out of the drive gear and case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302960">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302960" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302960" filename="../figg13/g1302960.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Pull Input Shaft Out of Drive Gear and Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the bushing in the pocket of the input shaft and replace if worn (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302961">Figure 61</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302961" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302961" filename="../figg13/g1302961.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 61. Check Bushing in Pocket of Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
